title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1990-02-25
description: Touch Of Gray-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Jack A Roe, Little Red Rooster, Stagger Lee, Queen Jane Approximately, The Last Time, Cassidy, Deal China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, A Little Light, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text: Feb. 25, 1990 Nice way to kick off 1990.  This is an enjoyable show.  It may not be the best of 1990, but it is solid.  The Cassidy-> Deal to end the first set rocks out nicely.  Estimated-> Eyes picks up steam, but I like the Wharf Rat-> Sugar.  Good sounding SBD.  Enjoy!
messed up sound levels the sound quality on the 1st set is not good.  volume levels were all over the place.  seems to be fixed on the 2nd set.  3 stars for quality

Nice show The sound problems you speak of are minor and part of the master tape. Although the mix is not the best. The show itself is good and worth a download.

3.5/5 for sound
3.75/5 for performance
I'll bump it up to 4 stars overall.

Nice Eyes It's one of those speedy ones. Segue from a nice Estimated is a little awkward, but Eyes gets really nice toward the middle.

Interesting jams throughout the second set. Wharf gets very psychedelic. Cool stuff!
